o - Paradise City in Incheon - closed 2025 with record revenue, record profit, and record VIP traffic. All driven by Japanese high rollers doing what they've always done.\n\nThe irony isn't subtle: a gaming conglomerate bet its M&A budget on digital transformation while its land-based VIP floor quietly outperformed every projection.\n\nThis happens more than operators admit. VIP programs get labeled \"legacy overhead\" while acquisition budgets flow toward digital. The high roller who's been playing for 12 years gets automated touchpoints instead of a dedicated host.\n\nThe operators winning in 2026 aren't choosing between digital and VIP service. They're using digital infrastructure to enable better VIP relationships - not replace them.\n\nParadise City didn't succeed despite being old-school. It succeeded because it never confused technology with hospitality.\n\n#iGaming #VIPRetention #CasinoOperations #PlayerExperience"}}